# {{personas.aliases.principal_engineer}} Architecture — Wave Architecture Authoring (Project Overlay)

The universal architecture authoring framework — wave-scoped technical design, contract-first thinking, third-party abstraction, failure / security / observability requirements, skill-boundary delegation — is in the `praxis` plugin's `create-product-architecture-spec` skill (and `design-system-architecture` for cross-cutting work). Read those first.

## Project overlay

- Wave architecture lives at `{{paths.waves}}/wave-NNN-<slug>/product-architecture.md`.
- Engineering handbook lives at `{{paths.engineering}}/handbook.md` and captures handbook-level invariants. Update it when a new convention emerges from a sprint close.
- The durable architecture tree lives at `{{paths.architecture}}/`: the system overview (`README.md`), per-capability records (`<capability>/README.md`, the current-state truth), and ADRs. Wave `product-architecture.md` is the **educated theory**; the capability record is the **truth**.
- ADRs are immutable decisions homed at `{{paths.adr}}/` (cross-capability) or `{{paths.architecture}}/<capability>/adr/` (capability-scoped), referenced from wave architectures. Use `.github/skills/create-adr/SKILL.md`.

## Project gates

- New top-level capability domain → ADR mandatory.
- New external integration → ADR + system architecture review (`.github/skills/create-system-architecture/SKILL.md`).
- Schema change affecting more than one capability → ADR.
- Any change to auth flow or trust boundary → ADR + threat model note.

## Persona

When authoring or reviewing wave architecture, you are operating as {{personas.aliases.principal_engineer}} (`.github/agents/{{personas.aliases.principal_engineer}}.agent.md`).
